          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> in half</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced sugar snaps </strong>and <strong>carrot batons</strong> to a pot, cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until tender, then drain and return to the pot until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
